metadata.name: WTBS Logo with Friends #15
metadata.description:
Did you know that WTBS is now sixth months old? If we were Will’s baby, we’d be sitting up and prepping to crawl — the literal baby steps that precede an entire lifetime of movement. 

Play is another integral part of our development. Play teaches us to connect, laugh, share, love, and learn. It helps form our earliest friendships that mold us into who we are destined to become. Over the last six months we have had the immense pleasure of forming new relationships with some of the amazing artists that comprise of the fxhash community. 

It is the love and support of new friends Laurent Houdard, Ada Ada Ada, elsif, and Camille Roux that made our first (official) collaboration possible. Thank you so much for the idea, the vision, the art, the time, and the wrangling to make this possible. 

Each letter is imbued with the unique style of an artist, based on a framework created by Laurent. There is a small chance of receiving a piece with two of the same style, with the rarest possibility of receiving one with all four quadrants the same. 

Collect with love and the knowledge that your support means the world to us. Thank you for listening every week, and for the messages and stories that you share with us. We can’t wait to continue to grow.

Thank you so much again to Laurent, Ada, elsif, and Camille. This is what community is.

metadata.name: Fragment Assembler #25
metadata.description:
Fragment Assembler is a chaos engine that creates complex abstract patterns and textures. As the artwork is drawn, it constantly recomposes itself during assembly with a series of displacement techniques, creating new forms and visual elements, while others get broken into pieces and textures. The work is orientation agnostic, and will display the output in portrait orientation on tall displays.

Intended to display on high resolution mode. The artwork renders with lower resolution by default to maintain compatibility with lower end devices. 

Press '2' to double the internal resolution (recommended).
Press 'h' to enable full internal resolution (requires a modern desktop computer).
Press space bar to reload the work.
Press 's' to save the output as PNG.
To render a 6k PNG, first press 'h', then save with 'p' (requires a modern desktop computer).


Made with p5.js & WebGL.
Best displayed with a modern desktop system & Chrome browser. 


Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: In the Edge #235
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: Duet #67
metadata.description:
by Daeinc
Aug 2022

Duet explores generative+computational motion and creates an almost infinite sequence of visual compositions. Two groups of shapes transform, merge, and split randomly. What can be disorienting starts to make sense as every element is animated from one to the other. This transition animation is what connects random pieces and creates a relationship between them. Each element is mathematically interpolated, with its motion defined by an equation. 

Although there are key moments, it is hard to summarize time-based work as a static image. As a constantly evolving generative motion piece, Duet invites viewers to form their impression by feeling the rhythm over time.

## Guide:
- The animation responds to window aspect ratio. It reproduces the same outcome at the same ratio. 
- For reliable playback, keep the window active and use IPFS view.
- See browser console for more info.
- Tested on MacOS 12.5.1 with Chromium 104.0

## Keyboard Interaction
- [n] to play a new random loop.
- [spacebar] to play/pause.
- [s] to save PNG. use URL params for dimensions.
- [up] and [down] to change shape resolution.
- [left] and [right] to change BPM. only works while looping. 
- [h] to toggle high DPI mode. off by default.
- [p] to toggle pixel snapping. off by default.

## URL Parameters
- add parameters separated by ampersand to the URL ex. https://.../?fxhash=...&w=1200&h=600
- [w] and [h]: set width and height in pixels. (ex. w=1200&h=600)
- [s] and [e]: set starting and ending keyframes (inclusive) for loop. (ex. s=20&e=24) 
- setting large values for start/end is not advised.
- [len]: instead of start/end, set a loop length between 1 and 16. (ex. len=4)
- [bpm]: beats per minute. (ex. bpm=80)
- [res]: shape resolution between 0 and 18. (ex. res=2)
- [pr]: pixel ratio. set it to 2 (or press [h]) for hi-DPI screens.
- [ar]: maximum aspect ratio. set to any value over 1. 1.2 by default.
- [snap]: add the param to snap to pixel grid.

## License
CC BY-NC 4.0
Please refer to the included LICENSE.md for license information.
Libraries used: canvas-sketch, canvas-sketch-util, dom-events, hsv2rgb, keyframes, equations from easings.net, array shuffle from stackoverflow.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. metadata.name: color combinations #131
metadata.description:
the 'color combinations' series was developed as an exercise of combining colors from a single defined palette and the attempt to make all 15 selected colors being able to work within each other.

the constant pursuit for perfectionism made me design more than 200 tentatives of creating a perfect circle, and therefore the circle is the rarest output for the series.

i hope this series serves as a reference and inspire everyone out there.

2,340 possible combinations.
the closer the shape to the circle the rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%.
the bigger the shape the rarer - ranging from 30% to 20%.
beige and black colors are rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%
